Package: gmeshd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, iproute2, nftables
Recommends: wireguard-tools
Description: Go-based WireGuard mesh networking daemon
 gmeshd manages a node's membership in a WireGuard mesh: it owns the
 WireGuard interface, runs STUN-based NAT discovery, performs hole
 punching and relay fallback, installs nftables firewall rules, and
 exposes a gRPC API on a Unix socket for local consumers.
 .
 This package ships the daemon (gmeshd), operator CLI (gmeshctl),
 relay server (gmesh-relay), and the systemd unit that supervises
 the daemon.
